    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The vampire squid\u2014so called for its red eyes and cloak-like webbing\u2014is a cephalopod from the lightless depths of the oceans. This eerie mollusk is covered in photophores, which it can use to create a defensive barrage of light when agitated.<br/><br/> A vampire squid can reach a total body length of up to 1 foot and weighs 1 pound."
        }
